thread.title: The 10-Point.

author: Gerard Baker
title: The 10-Point.
text:
Good morning on this Good Friday and Passover,
Dial M for Merger
Walmart is in early talks to buy insurer Humana in a deal that would turn the retail behemoth overnight into one of the nation’s largest health insurers, the Journal reported exclusively Thursday night. If completed, it would be another huge development in the continuing reshaping of the U.S. health-care and retail sectors. It isn’t clear what terms the companies are discussing, but any deal would be big, given Humana’s $37 billion market capitalization. And it...
